                  <hi rend="italic">Witnesses for the Defence.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18740407-name-442" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18740407-name-442" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18740407-name-442" type="surname" value="HAYWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18740407-name-442" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>JANE HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner was at work on the 23rd February, and on the 24th he was in bed all day—he was not well—he got up on the morning of the 25th to go to the county court at Greenwich.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> The 24th of February was Tuesday, as well as I recollect.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18740407-name-443" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18740407-name-443" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18740407-name-443" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18740407-name-443" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN ANDREWS</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner went to bed on the 23rd February, at nine o'clock at night, and on the 24th he was in bed all day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> I remember those particular days because my husband was away from home—the prisoner has lived with me since he has been home from the north.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">By</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">THE COURT</hi>. I was not present in the police court at Greenwich when he was tried on this charge, but I was there when he was charged with loitering on a gentleman's footpath, and he got off.</p>
